Pour the @water{240%ml} for the couscous and half the @chicken stock paste{20%g} into a 
#medium saucepan{} and bring to the boil.

When boiling, remove from the heat, stir in the @couscous{120%g} and pop a lid on the 
#pan{}. Leave to the side for ~{8-10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin 
strips.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Heat a drizzle of oil 
in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{390%g} and sliced pepper. 
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir-fry until the chicken is browned all over and 
the pepper starts to soften, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Add the garlic, @Caribbean style jerk{1%sachet} and @tomato puree{30%g} to the pan. 
Stir-fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir the @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water for the sauce{150%ml}, @mango chutney{40%g} and 
remaining chicken stock paste into the pan. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and 
simmer gently until the sauce has thickened and the chicken is cooked through, 
~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Add a splash of water if it looks a little too thick.

In the meantime, trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{2}. Zest and cut the @lime{1} 
into wedges.

Cut the @medium tomato{1} into 1cm chunks and pop into a #medium bowl{}. Add the spring 
onion, a drizzle of oil and a squeeze of lime juice. Season with salt and pepper, then 
set your salsa aside.

Once the couscous is ready, fluff it with a #fork{} and stir through the lime zest.

Once the sauce has thickened, add a squeeze of lime juice and season with salt and 
pepper. Add a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Share the couscous out between your bowls and spoon over the chicken and pepper stew.

Top with the salsa to finish and serve with any remaining lime wedges for squeezing over. 
Enjoy!